'''Fabrice d'Almeida'''(born 15 November 1963) is a [[France|French]] historian. His expertise lies in history of the media, image propaganda and manipulation.

After receiving his master's degree from the [[Sorbonne]] and [[Sciences Po]], he earned a Ph.D from the [[Paris West University Nanterre La Défense]]. As a fellow of the École Française de Rome, he initiated the study of  socialism in France and Italy therefore becoming one of the first comparative historians in France. He was invited to the TU-Berlin in Germany as a guest professor as the recipient of the Alexander von Humboldt fellowship, under the supervision of [[Jürgen Kocka]] and [[:de:Hartmut Kaelble|Harmut Kaelble]] (ZVGE). D'Almeida also  spent  two years in Berlin at the Marc Bloch Center. Upon his return to Paris he was promoted to director of the Institut d’Histoire du Temps Présent (IHTP CNRS) and was then elected to be full professor at [[Panthéon-Assas University]]. He is now the director of  Master Media and Globalization at the University.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ifp.u-paris2.fr/37238164/0/fiche___pagelibre/&RH=IFP-ENSEIG|title=IFP : Institut Français de Presse - D'Almeida Fabrice|first=isabelle|last=Demier|website=ifp.u-paris2.fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ifp.u-paris2.fr/22188893/0/fiche___pagelibre/&RH=IFP-ENSEIG|title=IFP : Institut Français de Presse - D'Almeida Fabrice|first=isabelle|last=Demier|website=ifp.u-paris2.fr}}</ref> He was appointed publisher at Albin Michel in January 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.livreshebdo.fr/article/albin-michel-fabrice-dalmeida-directeur-litteraire|title=Albin Michel : Fabrice d’Almeida, directeur littéraire|publisher=}}</ref>

His work with [[:fr:Anthony Rowley|Antony Rowley]], ''Et si on refaisait l’histoire ?'' is a reflection on French history. It is one of  the first "What-If?" genre histories in France.<ref>http://www.odilejacob.com/catalogue/history-and-geopolitics/asking-quotwhat-ifquot-in-history_9782738126375.php</ref>

The work of Fabrice d'Almeida was brought to the attention of the general public through the release of several documentaries and TV films such as "Love, Hate, and Propaganda." (CBC-Toronto)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm3948180/|title=Fabrice d'Almeida|website=IMDb}}</ref>

His book ''High Society Under the Third Reich'' is the first systematic study of the relationship between German high society and the Nazis. It uses unpublished archival material, private diaries and diplomatic documents to explore the hidden areas of power where privileges, tax breaks, and stolen property were exchanged.<ref>http://eu.wiley.com/WileyCDA/WileyTitle/productCd-0745643124.html</ref>
His most recently published book in France focused on the management of the SS concentration camp guards.

