'''Manfred Berg''' is a German historian who serves as the Curt Engelhorn Chair in American History at [[Heidelberg University]].<ref name=hu>{{cite web|title=Curt Engelhorn Chair in American History|url=http://www.uni-heidelberg.de/fakultaeten/philosophie/zegk/schurman/lehrstuhl/schurman_mitarbeiter_eng.html|work=Uni-heidelberg.de|publisher=Heidelberg University|accessdate=12 April 2012}}</ref> He has also served as Heidelberg University's dean of faculty.<ref name=tie>{{cite news|title=Another German politician stripped of doctorate degree for plagiarism|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/another-german-politician-stripped-of-doctorate-degree-for-plagiarism/804461/1|accessdate=12 April 2012|newspaper=The Indian Express|date=16 June 2011}}</ref> He previously taught at the [[Free University of Berlin]]<ref name=npr>{{cite news|title=War in Iraq? Views from Egypt, Germany|url=https://www.npr.org/programs/morning/transcripts/2002/dec/021212.edwards.html|accessdate=12 April 2012|date=12 December 2002|agency=National Public Radio}}</ref> and served at the [[German Historical Institute]] in [[Washington D.C.]]<ref name=slpd>{{cite news|last=Koenig|first=Robert|title=Clinton, Kohl to Focus on Russia|url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=SL&p_theme=sl&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EB04E0E5FBF2362&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM|accessdate=12 April 2012|newspaper=St. Louis Post-Dispatch|date=26 March 1993}}</ref>
Since spring 2017, Berg is speaker of the ''Graduiertenkolleg'' "Authority and Trust in American Culture Society, History, and Politics"<ref>http://www.hca.uni-heidelberg.de/gkat/index.html</ref> (GKAT) at the [[Heidelberg Center for American Studies]] (HCA).
